de.mdelab.simulator.mrubis.injectors

Class NoCF2_Injector

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.mdelab.simulator.mrubis.injectors.AbstractCF2_Injector
      • de.mdelab.simulator.mrubis.injectors.NoCF2_Injector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Injector<ProvidedInterface>

    public class NoCF2_Injector
extends AbstractCF2_Injector
    Does not inject a CF2 but it creates and adds Exceptions to the given ProvidedInterface if the component providing the interface is started (see ComponentState.STARTED) and if at least one started component is using the provided interface. The number of exception added is below the given threshold that would otherwise cause a CF2.
    Version:
    0.41
    Author:
    thomas vogel
